HTML/HTML5  - Hyper text mark up language
            - html is used to build the static web pages
            - Current version of html is html 5
CSS/CSS3   - casecading style sheet
           - is used to apply the styles to static web pages
           - color
           - border
           - height 
           - width
           - etc
           - current version of css is css3
JavaScript - Current version of javascript is ES12
           - javascript is a scripting language
           - is used to convert the static web page to dynamic web pages
Day-2:
======
HTML
=====
Hyper text markup language 
html released by Tim Berners Lee(one of microsoft employee)
html used to build static web pages
html saves with the extension of .html or .htm
suggestable IDE for html is visual code is also called vscodeit is a open source IDE
we will execute the html by using browsers like gooleChrome, Opera
we will build the web pages by using tags
<html>
<head>
<title>
<body>
-----
-----
above tags provided by vendor

html 1.0 ---1991
html 5--- 2008
Html 5.X stable in the market reason is supporting API's like
->storages
->web workers
->Web socket
->Geolocation
->Drag & Drop

Day-3:
======
Stucture of the webpages
========================

DOCTYPE

ROOT ELEMENT

        HEAD SECTION / META SECTION
        BODY SECTION / MAIN SECTION

- DOCTYPE representing the version of html
- we will represent "HTML5" following DOCTYPE
  <!DOCTYPE html>
- <html> </html> tag represent the root section
- <head> </head> tag represent the header section
- head section used to represent the "METADATA"
  Ex:
  author
  verssion
  title
  -----
  ----
  - body section used to represent the main content of the webpage
  paragraphs
  tables
  division
  images

  Ex:
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html>
      <head>
            //META DATA
            //<meta> tag used to define the metadata
      </head>
      <body>
            // to define the main contents
            //images
            //paragraphs
            //tables
            //forms
      </body>
  </html>
  
  Day-4:
  ======
  headings:
  <h1></h1>     ---- Main heading
  <h2></h2>     ---- Sub heading
  <h3></h3>              "
  <h4></h4>              "
  <h5></h5>              "
  <h6></h6>              "

  padding -- inside box itself maintain the gap/freespace
  border = 30px solid red {Lines}
         = 30px dotted red {dotted lines}
  border radius - to change corners in radius
  width = 30% - to occupy 30%
  margin = auto - content in middle
         = 30% auto- 30% to maintain space
  box-shadow = 0 0 10px red;
             = x y  z (directions)    
  text-shadow = 0 0 10px blue;
              = x y z(directions)
  padding, border,border radius this all attributes
  right side is all values   

Paragraphs
==========
  <p></p> tag used to define the paragraphs
  background : linear-gradient(45deg, red, black)= combination of 2 colours
  font-family : to change the fonts for text
  display : inline-block -- side by side
          : block --none by one

Day-5
=====
division tag used to define the sections / divisions in webpages
padding -- inside gap
margin -- outside gap

marquee
=======
To scroll the content or text
direction= to scroll which direction
scrollamount= speed of scrolling


